{
    "title": "Dilly Bread",
    "categories": ["Breads"],
    "author": "Helen Minkiewitz (Nonny)",
    "content": [
        {
            "markdown": [
                "Soften and mix together and let stand for 10 minutes:"
            ]
        },
        {
            "ingredients": [
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "dry yeast"},
                {"amount": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "name": "lukewarm water"},
                {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "sugar"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "markdown": [
                "Add and stir in:"
            ]
        },
        {
            "ingredients": [
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "small curd cottage cheese, warmed"},
                {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "yellow onion, minced"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "butter, softened"},
                {"amount": 2, "unit": "tsp", "name": "dill seed"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "egg, beaten"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "markdown": [
                "Mix in to form a sticky dough:"
            ]
        },
        {
            "ingredients": [
                {"amount": 2.25, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                {"amount": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "name": "baking soda"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "markdown": [
                "Turn dough in a greased bowl and allow to rise until double in volume. Stir dough down, place",
                "in a greased loaf pan and allow to rise until double again.",
                "",
                "Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when thumped. Remove from the oven,",
                "brush with butter and sprinkle with kosher salt. Cool in the pan for 15 minutes, then run a knife",
                "blade around the edge, and remove from the loaf pan. Cut the loaf in thick slices and serve hot with",
                "butter and lentil soup."
            ]
        }
    ]
}
